ZH: 我的爷爷会套马。
EN: My grandfather knows how to ride horses.

ZH: 他正在学习如何套马。
EN: He is learning how to ride horses.

ZH: 这个男孩非常喜欢套马。
EN: This boy really enjoys riding horses.

ZH: 她套马的技巧非常高超。
EN: Her horse riding skills are very advanced.

ZH: 我们会跟着指导员一起套马。
EN: We will ride horses together with the instructor.

ZH: 我们在农场上套马。
EN: We are riding horses on the farm.

ZH: 他曾经参加过一场套马比赛。
EN: He has participated in a horse riding competition before.

ZH: 她正在考虑学习套马的技能。
EN: She is considering learning horse riding skills.

ZH: 这个地方提供套马的训练课程。
EN: This place offers horse riding training courses.

ZH: 她希望能够更加熟练地套马。
EN: She hopes to become more skilled at riding horses.

ZH: 你需要多久才能够学会套马？
EN: How long will it take for you to learn how to ride horses?

ZH: 套马需要耐心和坚持不懈的训练。
EN: Riding horses requires patience and persistent training.

ZH: 他在套马的时候充满了自信。
EN: He is full of confidence when riding horses.

ZH: 她每个周末都会去套马俱乐部。
EN: She goes to the horse riding club every weekend.

ZH: 这个小女孩正在向父亲学习套马。
EN: This little girl is learning horse riding from her father.

ZH: 刚开始套马时，需要有人帮助你。
EN: When starting to ride horses, you need someone to assist you.

ZH: 他已经能够独自套马了。
EN: He can ride horses alone now.

ZH: 她和朋友们一起套马度过了愉快的时光。
EN: She had a great time riding horses with her friends.

ZH: 这匹马非常乖巧，适合新手套马。
EN: This horse is very gentle, suitable for beginners to ride.

ZH: 我累了一天，决定套马放松一下。
EN: After a tiring day, I decided to relax by riding a horse.
